1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:01,450
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,450 --> 00:00:02,783
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:03,803 --> 00:00:05,303
Joy is my child
that I created and raised...

4
00:00:05,303 --> 00:00:07,003
and brought into this world.

5
00:00:07,003 --> 00:00:08,403
So give her back.

6
00:00:09,236 --> 00:00:10,903
I don't need money or anything else.

7
00:00:10,903 --> 00:00:13,003
Just give me back my baby, Joy.

8
00:00:13,003 --> 00:00:14,603
- Please!
- Look.

9
00:00:14,603 --> 00:00:17,603
I have nothing to do with Joy or whatever.

10
00:00:19,536 --> 00:00:21,203
Give her back!

11
00:00:21,203 --> 00:00:25,136
Give me back my baby!

12
00:00:25,136 --> 00:00:28,336
- Give me back my baby.
- What's going on?

13
00:00:28,336 --> 00:00:30,503
- Give me back my baby.
- Did that man dump her?

14
00:00:30,503 --> 00:00:32,103
- What's happening?
- That's my baby.

15
00:00:32,103 --> 00:00:33,703
- That's not it.
- Give me back.

16
00:00:33,703 --> 00:00:35,969
- Give me back my baby!
- That's not it.

17
00:00:35,969 --> 00:00:37,736
- Please.
- I told you, it's not me.

18
00:00:37,736 --> 00:00:39,203
Give me back!

19
00:00:39,203 --> 00:00:41,403
Give me back my baby!

20
00:00:42,103 --> 00:00:43,436
- Give me back my baby!
- What's with this woman?

21
00:00:43,436 --> 00:00:46,203
It's my baby, give her back.

22
00:00:46,203 --> 00:00:48,203
Just give me my baby back.

23
00:00:48,203 --> 00:00:50,003
Please, okay?

24
00:00:50,003 --> 00:00:51,736
You Darn CPO!

25
00:00:51,736 --> 00:00:53,803
Give me back my baby!

26
00:00:58,603 --> 00:01:00,103
Stop right there!

27
00:01:00,103 --> 00:01:02,803
I said stop right there!

28
00:01:03,836 --> 00:01:05,403
Wait.

29
00:01:05,403 --> 00:01:07,503
But why am I running away?

30
00:01:08,136 --> 00:01:10,436
It's not me, so why should I?

31
00:01:39,903 --> 00:01:41,636
I remember you.

32
00:01:44,003 --> 00:01:46,036
You helped me in the lobby before, right?

33
00:01:46,036 --> 00:01:48,636
Listen carefully, I won't say this twice.

34
00:01:48,636 --> 00:01:50,903
I'm not the CPO you're talking about.

35
00:01:52,303 --> 00:01:53,336
What are you saying?

36
00:01:54,636 --> 00:01:58,436
Strategic Planning Division,
TF Team Two Leader, Ko Gyeol?

37
00:01:58,436 --> 00:02:00,203
That's right. I'm not the CPO,

38
00:02:00,203 --> 00:02:02,636
I'm a team leader in Strategic Planning.
Got it?

39
00:02:03,436 --> 00:02:05,103
You're really not the CPO?

40
00:02:05,836 --> 00:02:07,803
I told you, I'm not.

41
00:02:07,803 --> 00:02:09,936
Then why were you pretending
to be the CPO yesterday?

42
00:02:09,936 --> 00:02:11,336
Who was pretending?

43
00:02:11,336 --> 00:02:13,236
You made all that fuss on your own.

44
00:02:13,236 --> 00:02:15,336
No, yesterday, in the CPO's office...

45
00:02:17,703 --> 00:02:19,736
If you are not the CPO,

46
00:02:19,736 --> 00:02:22,503
- you should've said so.
- Did you even give me a chance to speak?

47
00:02:22,503 --> 00:02:25,036
You kicked me out of nowhere
and made my nose bleed!

48
00:02:28,703 --> 00:02:30,403
- What's this?
- What is this?

49
00:02:30,403 --> 00:02:32,836
My goodness!
Isn't that Team Leader Ko Gyeol?

50
00:02:32,836 --> 00:02:35,069
- Who is that woman?
- I don't know.

51
00:02:36,303 --> 00:02:36,936
What's going on?

52
00:02:37,536 --> 00:02:39,936
Ms. Seo,
please check the company intranet.

53
00:02:48,936 --> 00:02:50,403
Good morning, everybody.

54
00:02:51,203 --> 00:02:52,703
Give her back.

55
00:02:52,703 --> 00:02:55,436
- Give me back my baby.
- What is it?

56
00:02:56,336 --> 00:02:59,236
It's my baby, give her back.

57
00:02:59,236 --> 00:03:01,503
- Give me back my baby!
- That's not it.

58
00:03:03,303 --> 00:03:05,703
New TF Team Two Leader proven to be a dad.

59
00:03:05,703 --> 00:03:07,803
A bad man who abandoned his woman
and took the child.

60
00:03:07,803 --> 00:03:09,436
Isn't he the worst?

61
00:03:09,436 --> 00:03:10,903
Are they shooting a movie at the company?

62
00:03:10,903 --> 00:03:12,103
She's saying it's the CPO, though.

63
00:03:12,103 --> 00:03:14,203
Stay neutral until facts are confirmed.

64
00:03:14,203 --> 00:03:15,203
Be careful of defamation.

65
00:03:17,103 --> 00:03:18,103
What is this?

66
00:03:18,603 --> 00:03:20,803
She seems to be the co-CEO
of Lucky Joy Tech.

67
00:03:23,703 --> 00:03:26,503
Now that you know for sure,
stop harassing innocent people.

68
00:03:26,503 --> 00:03:27,503
Understood?

69
00:03:28,036 --> 00:03:30,103
I heard it was a legal acquisition.

70
00:03:30,103 --> 00:03:31,303
If you feel wronged,

71
00:03:31,303 --> 00:03:33,436
prepare properly and take legal action.

72
00:03:33,436 --> 00:03:36,103
Do you think rushing in like this
will solve anything?

73
00:03:36,103 --> 00:03:37,536
Legal action?

74
00:03:45,436 --> 00:03:47,103
Yes, Chief.

75
00:03:48,203 --> 00:03:49,203
I'm with her.

76
00:03:50,603 --> 00:03:51,736
Yes, understood.

77
00:03:52,803 --> 00:03:55,003
Was that the real CPO?

78
00:03:55,003 --> 00:03:56,803
Yes, he's waiting.

79
00:03:56,803 --> 00:03:58,803
Go and sort it out properly
with the person involved.

80
00:04:00,136 --> 00:04:01,403
I'm sorry.

81
00:04:01,403 --> 00:04:05,036
For what I did yesterday and today...

82
00:04:08,903 --> 00:04:10,069
And here.

83
00:04:11,403 --> 00:04:13,703
How do you have this?

84
00:04:14,936 --> 00:04:16,103
The airport that day.

85
00:04:16,103 --> 00:04:17,136
You accused me of pickpocketing, right?

86
00:04:17,803 --> 00:04:20,436
That's right.
There was a misunderstanding that day.

87
00:04:20,436 --> 00:04:21,836
The bracelet fell off then.

88
00:04:21,836 --> 00:04:23,103
That's a relief.

89
00:04:23,103 --> 00:04:25,236
I thought I lost it and looked everywhere.

90
00:04:27,503 --> 00:04:30,603
Then we both
misunderstood each other once,

91
00:04:30,603 --> 00:04:31,803
so let's call it even.

92
00:04:33,203 --> 00:04:35,236
Even.

93
00:04:36,403 --> 00:04:37,403
Forget it.

94
00:04:37,836 --> 00:04:39,636
Let's not get involved again, okay?

95
00:04:41,436 --> 00:04:42,536
Excuse me.

96
00:04:42,536 --> 00:04:45,003
Could you walk with me just to the lobby?

97
00:04:45,003 --> 00:04:47,803
I might get dragged out again.

98
00:04:49,336 --> 00:04:51,003
(Lucky Joy Tech CEOs,
Cho Eun Ae, Han Ji Hun)

99
00:04:56,203 --> 00:04:57,636
As you can see,

100
00:04:57,636 --> 00:04:59,803
the stamp is on here,

101
00:04:59,803 --> 00:05:01,703
but you're saying
you didn't stamp it yourself?

102
00:05:02,903 --> 00:05:05,936
Therefore, you want
the contract declared null and void?

103
00:05:05,936 --> 00:05:07,803
Yes, exactly.

104
00:05:07,803 --> 00:05:09,436
Do you think that's possible?

105
00:05:09,903 --> 00:05:13,603
I thought it was just investment documents
from Kangsu Construction.

106
00:05:13,603 --> 00:05:15,003
If I had known it was a sale contract,

107
00:05:15,003 --> 00:05:16,903
I would've burned the papers.

108
00:05:16,903 --> 00:05:19,003
That's your concern.

109
00:05:19,003 --> 00:05:21,403
You want us to return a program
that now belongs to Kangsu Construction?

110
00:05:22,103 --> 00:05:23,003
That is just ridiculous.

111
00:05:23,603 --> 00:05:26,603
I know, it's clearly my mistake.

112
00:05:26,603 --> 00:05:28,836
That's why I'm here making this request.

113
00:05:28,836 --> 00:05:31,703
Could you nullify this contract, please?

114
00:05:32,136 --> 00:05:33,403
Are you joking?

115
00:05:34,103 --> 00:05:36,136
It's a program I devoted my youth to.

116
00:05:36,136 --> 00:05:37,803
I can never give up my Joy.

117
00:05:37,803 --> 00:05:39,503
And if you don't?

118
00:05:39,503 --> 00:05:43,503
Are you going to start a legal dispute
against Kangsu Construction?

119
00:05:44,203 --> 00:05:45,736
A legal dispute?

120
00:05:45,736 --> 00:05:49,003
No, I can live without the law,
so I wouldn't go that far.

121
00:05:51,436 --> 00:05:53,903
What I mean is,

122
00:05:53,903 --> 00:05:57,436
I'm a very law-abiding person...

123
00:05:57,436 --> 00:05:59,236
Law-abiding?

124
00:05:59,236 --> 00:06:02,636
Is that why you
wrecked my office yesterday?

125
00:06:05,036 --> 00:06:06,903
- Legal team?
- Yes.

126
00:06:06,903 --> 00:06:08,203
The legal notice I mentioned yesterday...

127
00:06:08,203 --> 00:06:09,203
We sent it yesterday.

128
00:06:09,203 --> 00:06:11,003
You sent it already?

129
00:06:11,003 --> 00:06:12,136
Okay.

130
00:06:13,536 --> 00:06:17,136
You will receive a legal notice today.

131
00:06:17,703 --> 00:06:19,603
What? A legal notice?

132
00:06:19,603 --> 00:06:21,503
Assault, obstruction of business,

133
00:06:21,503 --> 00:06:23,503
trespassing, property damage,

134
00:06:23,503 --> 00:06:24,736
defamation!

135
00:06:25,703 --> 00:06:26,636
Shall I go on?

136
00:06:27,403 --> 00:06:28,836
Chief.

137
00:06:32,136 --> 00:06:33,236
An envelope?

138
00:06:34,403 --> 00:06:35,903
From Kangsu Construction's legal team?

139
00:06:37,336 --> 00:06:41,436
This must be
the investment confirmation documents.

140
00:06:48,803 --> 00:06:50,203
Hey, Eun Ae.

141
00:06:51,403 --> 00:06:52,803
Yeah, I just got it.

142
00:06:52,803 --> 00:06:54,603
Did you open it?

143
00:06:54,603 --> 00:06:56,236
Why? Should I?

144
00:06:56,236 --> 00:06:57,303
Are you curious about what's inside?

145
00:06:57,303 --> 00:06:59,803
No, absolutely not.

146
00:07:00,336 --> 00:07:02,003
I'll open it myself.

147
00:07:02,003 --> 00:07:04,703
Is this
the official investment confirmation?

148
00:07:04,703 --> 00:07:06,103
I'll leave it in your room.

149
00:07:09,136 --> 00:07:11,836
Every dog has its day.

150
00:07:12,536 --> 00:07:14,203
I can finally relax a bit.

151
00:07:17,803 --> 00:07:19,603
What do I do?

152
00:07:19,603 --> 00:07:20,803
I failed to persuade him...

153
00:07:20,803 --> 00:07:22,403
Right, the legal notice.

154
00:07:26,803 --> 00:07:28,936
Darn it. Her again.

155
00:07:33,303 --> 00:07:34,836
Good morning.

156
00:07:47,336 --> 00:07:49,936
(New TF Team Two Leader is a father,
a bad man who took the child!)

157
00:07:53,103 --> 00:07:55,503
There are strict internal rules
against fake news,

158
00:07:55,503 --> 00:07:56,536
so it'll die down soon.

159
00:07:57,803 --> 00:08:00,803
By the way,
do you happen to know anything...

160
00:08:00,803 --> 00:08:02,103
about the sale of Lucky Joy Tech?

161
00:08:03,136 --> 00:08:04,303
I'm the person in charge,

162
00:08:04,303 --> 00:08:07,003
but I failed to confirm
the co-developer's consent.

163
00:08:07,003 --> 00:08:08,803
So we're not entirely free
of responsibility.

164
00:08:10,003 --> 00:08:12,136
Could I take a look at that program?

165
00:08:12,603 --> 00:08:13,736
Of course.

166
00:08:26,336 --> 00:08:27,236
Come on in.

167
00:08:28,603 --> 00:08:30,303
Look who it is. Come on in.

168
00:08:30,836 --> 00:08:32,603
I'm on duty. Why did you call me?

169
00:08:32,603 --> 00:08:34,336
Sit down first. Let's talk.

170
00:08:34,336 --> 00:08:36,203
Sit.

171
00:08:38,803 --> 00:08:41,636
I've already spoken to General Affairs,

172
00:08:41,636 --> 00:08:44,336
so starting today,
you don't have to clean other areas.

173
00:08:45,303 --> 00:08:46,803
Tell them to just go back
to how it was before.

174
00:08:46,803 --> 00:08:47,903
It makes me uncomfortable.

175
00:08:48,603 --> 00:08:52,336
You're still as stubborn as ever.

176
00:08:52,336 --> 00:08:55,203
Let's have dinner tonight with Gwon Sik.

177
00:08:56,103 --> 00:08:57,636
If you keep this up,

178
00:08:57,636 --> 00:08:59,603
I'll take it as you telling me to quit.

179
00:08:59,603 --> 00:09:01,636
It's been decades since we met.

180
00:09:01,636 --> 00:09:02,936
Can't we at least have a meal together?

181
00:09:02,936 --> 00:09:04,436
Is that all our friendship is worth?

182
00:09:08,136 --> 00:09:11,103
Mr. Seo, keep your evening free.

183
00:09:11,103 --> 00:09:12,536
No excuses.

184
00:09:15,036 --> 00:09:16,236
Pick Bit Na up from kindergarten?

185
00:09:16,236 --> 00:09:17,203
Yes.

186
00:09:18,303 --> 00:09:20,736
The department head
asked to see me after class,

187
00:09:20,736 --> 00:09:22,003
so I don't think I can make it.

188
00:09:22,803 --> 00:09:25,436
Okay, I'll pick her up and bring her home.

189
00:09:25,436 --> 00:09:28,403
Why does the department head
want to see you?

190
00:09:28,403 --> 00:09:30,603
Did your appointment get confirmed?

191
00:09:31,703 --> 00:09:33,403
I'm not sure.

192
00:09:33,403 --> 00:09:35,003
I'll find out when I meet him.

193
00:09:35,703 --> 00:09:39,236
It must be good news.
I had a great dream last night.

194
00:09:40,203 --> 00:09:41,836
Professor,

195
00:09:41,836 --> 00:09:44,003
call me right away if there's good news.

196
00:09:49,536 --> 00:09:52,503
Where's the envelope
from Kangsu Construction?

197
00:09:53,103 --> 00:09:54,936
- On your desk.
- Thanks, Mom!

198
00:09:56,503 --> 00:09:58,936
What's the rush?

199
00:09:58,936 --> 00:10:00,703
(Legal Notice)

200
00:10:00,703 --> 00:10:03,736
(Request for Action on Illegal Acts)

201
00:10:05,836 --> 00:10:08,303
Joy, what should I do?

202
00:10:08,303 --> 00:10:09,603
Trying to get you back,

203
00:10:09,603 --> 00:10:11,636
I might end up with a permanent record.

204
00:10:12,203 --> 00:10:14,603
A permanent record...

205
00:10:14,603 --> 00:10:17,003
means having legal trouble...

206
00:10:17,003 --> 00:10:20,803
and leaving a serious stain on your life.

207
00:10:20,803 --> 00:10:22,336
Don't worry.

208
00:10:22,336 --> 00:10:24,303
It's not literal.

209
00:10:24,303 --> 00:10:27,136
More importantly,

210
00:10:27,136 --> 00:10:30,003
there's no way to get you back.

211
00:10:30,003 --> 00:10:31,303
Seriously...

212
00:10:33,203 --> 00:10:34,803
(Ji Hun)

213
00:10:34,803 --> 00:10:36,503
Darn it.

214
00:10:38,103 --> 00:10:39,603
Hello?

215
00:10:39,603 --> 00:10:40,803
What? Where?

216
00:10:45,803 --> 00:10:48,336
What makes you think you can come here?

217
00:10:48,336 --> 00:10:49,836
Then what am I supposed to do?

218
00:10:50,103 --> 00:10:52,436
You ignored all my texts and calls.

219
00:10:52,436 --> 00:10:55,036
Cho Eun Ae, please help me this once.

220
00:10:55,036 --> 00:10:56,036
What?

221
00:10:56,036 --> 00:10:58,503
I heard you've been protesting
in front of Kangsu Construction every day.

222
00:10:58,503 --> 00:11:00,203
I start work next week,

223
00:11:00,203 --> 00:11:03,136
and because of you,
my job offer might fall through.

224
00:11:03,136 --> 00:11:04,203
So?

225
00:11:04,203 --> 00:11:05,903
You want me to help you get hired...

226
00:11:05,903 --> 00:11:08,403
so you can raise Joy in my stead?

227
00:11:11,703 --> 00:11:13,203
This is half the sale amount.

228
00:11:13,203 --> 00:11:14,803
Since you didn't give me
your account number,

229
00:11:14,803 --> 00:11:15,903
I issued a check.

230
00:11:16,436 --> 00:11:20,603
- Just think of it as saving someone.
- I can't believe this.

231
00:11:20,603 --> 00:11:23,603
The more I listen,
the more ridiculous this gets.

232
00:11:23,603 --> 00:11:26,603
What is wrong with you?

233
00:11:26,603 --> 00:11:28,303
It's none of your business.

234
00:11:28,303 --> 00:11:30,503
None of my business?

235
00:11:31,103 --> 00:11:32,736
Didn't I tell you who I am?

236
00:11:32,736 --> 00:11:35,803
I'm a special employee at Lucky Joy Tech.

237
00:11:37,703 --> 00:11:39,736
This is unbelievable.

238
00:11:39,736 --> 00:11:41,703
Unbelievable? Want a taste?

239
00:11:42,303 --> 00:11:43,403
Cho Rong, stop.

240
00:11:44,536 --> 00:11:45,536
You should leave.

241
00:11:45,536 --> 00:11:48,236
If you come again, I won't let it slide.

242
00:11:48,703 --> 00:11:50,603
Eun Ae, please!

243
00:11:55,703 --> 00:11:57,303
Hey!

244
00:12:00,136 --> 00:12:01,903
Are you really going to be like this?

245
00:12:01,903 --> 00:12:03,636
Eun Ae, move.

246
00:12:03,636 --> 00:12:06,003
A crazy dog like this needs a beating.

247
00:12:08,703 --> 00:12:10,636
Birds of a feather flock together.

248
00:12:11,103 --> 00:12:14,003
Come one more time, and you'll regret it.

249
00:12:16,603 --> 00:12:19,536
Why did you bring that?

250
00:12:20,036 --> 00:12:23,403
Where did it go?

251
00:12:24,203 --> 00:12:26,503
It's not like it has legs.

252
00:12:26,503 --> 00:12:28,203
How strange.

253
00:12:30,303 --> 00:12:32,903
That tiny little bastard.

254
00:12:32,903 --> 00:12:33,836
What are you looking for, Grandma?

255
00:12:33,836 --> 00:12:36,403
Have you seen the handle?

256
00:12:37,703 --> 00:12:39,836
Is this the handle?

257
00:12:39,836 --> 00:12:43,403
Why did you take that with you?

258
00:12:44,236 --> 00:12:46,736
Grandma,
I'll be at Eun Ae's place for a bit.

259
00:12:46,736 --> 00:12:47,803
As for the mung beans,

260
00:12:47,803 --> 00:12:49,803
I'll grind them when I get back.

261
00:12:51,003 --> 00:12:53,003
All right, have fun.

262
00:12:53,003 --> 00:12:54,103
My goodness.

263
00:12:56,336 --> 00:12:59,703
<i>Chirp, chirp</i>

264
00:13:02,803 --> 00:13:05,403
Now they're saying
they'll take legal action.

265
00:13:06,303 --> 00:13:08,003
Do you know any lawyers?

266
00:13:08,003 --> 00:13:11,003
If I did, I would've already gone to them.

267
00:13:11,736 --> 00:13:13,503
What about asking Eun Hyeong?

268
00:13:13,503 --> 00:13:15,403
He must have at least one lawyer friend.

269
00:13:15,703 --> 00:13:17,603
If he finds out, Mom will too.

270
00:13:17,603 --> 00:13:18,836
No, that won't work.

271
00:13:23,903 --> 00:13:27,203
What about looking into places like this?

272
00:13:27,736 --> 00:13:28,836
Where?

273
00:13:30,303 --> 00:13:32,336
(Legal consultation always welcome)

274
00:13:32,336 --> 00:13:33,736
Bring the contract documents.

275
00:13:33,736 --> 00:13:36,303
We need to know the details
to help you legally.

276
00:13:40,303 --> 00:13:43,703
How am I supposed to get those documents?

277
00:13:54,203 --> 00:13:56,536
Look at this contract...

278
00:13:57,403 --> 00:13:59,403
There's no solution, none at all.

279
00:14:03,503 --> 00:14:05,836
(Joy,
the AI friend for ten million seniors)

280
00:14:06,936 --> 00:14:08,403
(AI conversation service)

281
00:14:11,836 --> 00:14:13,403
(Joy's universe)

282
00:14:13,403 --> 00:14:15,703
(Investment and business overview)

283
00:14:21,603 --> 00:14:23,736
Drink this milk and take your time eating.

284
00:14:23,736 --> 00:14:24,736
Okay.

285
00:14:29,236 --> 00:14:33,003
How did Professor Cho
become such a master homemaker?

286
00:14:34,136 --> 00:14:36,336
What's a master homemaker, Grandma?

287
00:14:37,736 --> 00:14:41,403
It means a pro
who's great at running a household.

288
00:14:42,003 --> 00:14:44,403
Dad isn't good at cooking.

289
00:14:44,403 --> 00:14:46,403
He always tries his best,

290
00:14:46,403 --> 00:14:47,703
but he says it's hard.

291
00:14:49,203 --> 00:14:51,103
Right.

292
00:14:51,103 --> 00:14:52,903
It's better that he's not good at it.

293
00:14:52,903 --> 00:14:56,136
If he were good at that too, I'd feel bad.

294
00:15:00,703 --> 00:15:02,136
What kind of ointment is this?

295
00:15:04,303 --> 00:15:07,203
Dad has hand eczema, so he uses this.

296
00:15:07,203 --> 00:15:08,736
Hand eczema?

297
00:15:16,003 --> 00:15:18,803
I should at least make some side dishes
so your dad has it easier.

298
00:15:29,903 --> 00:15:31,803
These are still here?

299
00:15:31,803 --> 00:15:33,303
It's been so long
since I brought anything over.

300
00:15:34,803 --> 00:15:37,603
Why is she so greedy for work?

301
00:15:38,503 --> 00:15:40,336
Who's greedy, Grandma?

302
00:15:43,136 --> 00:15:46,803
I'm talking about the greedy character
in the drama I'm watching.

303
00:15:56,336 --> 00:15:58,036
My goodness.

304
00:15:58,036 --> 00:15:59,203
Ow, my legs.

305
00:16:03,203 --> 00:16:04,703
Mom!

306
00:16:04,703 --> 00:16:06,103
Sweetie!

307
00:16:06,103 --> 00:16:09,136
- Bit Na, have you been well?
- Yes.

308
00:16:12,603 --> 00:16:14,303
Wait a second.

309
00:16:18,036 --> 00:16:19,036
You're back?

310
00:16:19,803 --> 00:16:21,136
You must be tired. Go change and come out.

311
00:16:21,136 --> 00:16:23,236
- I steamed some sweet potatoes.
- Mother.

312
00:16:24,003 --> 00:16:25,036
I'd like to talk to you.

313
00:16:25,836 --> 00:16:28,203
Talk? Sure.

314
00:16:28,736 --> 00:16:32,103
Eun Hyeong should have good news today.

315
00:16:33,703 --> 00:16:35,936
He must be meeting
the department head now.

316
00:16:37,003 --> 00:16:41,403
He might finally become
Professor Cho Eun Hyeong.

317
00:16:42,636 --> 00:16:43,836
Sorry?

318
00:16:44,936 --> 00:16:45,936
The philosophy department
is being abolished?

319
00:16:46,503 --> 00:16:48,303
You know how...

320
00:16:48,303 --> 00:16:51,136
the humanities are treated these days.

321
00:16:52,036 --> 00:16:55,103
Departments with no job prospects
have no reason to exist.

322
00:17:00,136 --> 00:17:01,536
What are you talking about?

323
00:17:01,536 --> 00:17:03,303
Refrain from visiting?

324
00:17:03,303 --> 00:17:07,203
Well, I know you're trying to help us,
Mother.

325
00:17:07,536 --> 00:17:09,603
But this is my home.

326
00:17:09,603 --> 00:17:12,803
The master bedroom, especially,
is my private space.

327
00:17:12,803 --> 00:17:14,403
Ji Seon,

328
00:17:14,403 --> 00:17:17,636
I just vacuumed the room
to make it easier for you.

329
00:17:17,636 --> 00:17:22,003
When you come, please come when I'm home.

330
00:17:22,003 --> 00:17:24,803
I came here because you were not home.

331
00:17:25,403 --> 00:17:26,903
I picked up Bit Na...

332
00:17:26,903 --> 00:17:29,036
and helped with the housework.
This isn't new.

333
00:17:29,703 --> 00:17:31,603
Bit Na is seven now.

334
00:17:31,603 --> 00:17:33,003
She can stay home alone, Mother.

335
00:17:33,603 --> 00:17:34,736
Ji Seon...

336
00:17:36,536 --> 00:17:38,003
Not going to work?

337
00:17:39,203 --> 00:17:40,503
No.

338
00:17:41,036 --> 00:17:44,803
I granted your wish, so now it's my turn.

339
00:17:44,803 --> 00:17:47,803
That doesn't count.

340
00:17:47,803 --> 00:17:50,003
It failed because Su Jeong came home.

341
00:17:50,003 --> 00:17:53,603
Still, you set the table for me.

342
00:17:54,503 --> 00:17:56,336
By the way,

343
00:17:56,336 --> 00:17:59,736
is your wish really
for me not to go to work?

344
00:17:59,736 --> 00:18:02,136
You've worked enough your whole life.

345
00:18:03,336 --> 00:18:06,136
You think the company
won't run without you?

346
00:18:06,136 --> 00:18:07,303
That's not true.

347
00:18:08,536 --> 00:18:13,303
If I stay home and don't go to work,

348
00:18:13,303 --> 00:18:15,503
will you hang out with me?

349
00:18:15,503 --> 00:18:18,003
What are you, a child?

350
00:18:18,503 --> 00:18:21,036
If I can't go to work...

351
00:18:21,036 --> 00:18:22,703
and you won't hang out with me,

352
00:18:22,703 --> 00:18:24,503
I'd be bored to death.

353
00:18:25,336 --> 00:18:27,036
Fine, I'll hang out with you.

354
00:18:29,636 --> 00:18:33,203
What do you want to do?

355
00:18:33,203 --> 00:18:34,803
Anywhere you want to go?

356
00:18:35,303 --> 00:18:36,903
Or anything you want to eat?

357
00:18:38,003 --> 00:18:40,536
Hold on, let me think this through...

358
00:18:40,536 --> 00:18:42,103
one by one.

359
00:18:44,603 --> 00:18:47,936
Is that pancake place we went to
still open?

360
00:18:49,503 --> 00:18:52,003
The one where they ground mung beans...

361
00:18:52,003 --> 00:18:56,403
and cooked them
with kimchi, pork, and bean sprouts...

362
00:18:57,603 --> 00:19:01,836
You know, the pancakes fried
on an upside-down pot lid.

363
00:19:01,836 --> 00:19:05,003
They used pork fat for the oil, right?

364
00:19:05,803 --> 00:19:08,303
Do you want those pancakes?

365
00:19:09,036 --> 00:19:10,403
No, it's just that...

366
00:19:12,403 --> 00:19:15,603
that's the only time...

367
00:19:15,603 --> 00:19:16,803
we ever ate out together.

368
00:19:17,303 --> 00:19:19,236
You remember everything.

369
00:19:20,303 --> 00:19:22,403
That place probably doesn't exist anymore.

370
00:19:23,203 --> 00:19:25,003
That neighborhood was redeveloped...

371
00:19:25,803 --> 00:19:28,103
a long time ago.

372
00:19:31,003 --> 00:19:32,903
Why was I so busy...

373
00:19:33,836 --> 00:19:36,303
that we never went out properly?

374
00:19:36,836 --> 00:19:39,803
We can start now.

375
00:19:39,803 --> 00:19:41,236
What's stopping us?

376
00:19:43,203 --> 00:19:44,403
Shall we, then?

377
00:19:45,403 --> 00:19:46,936
Apologize to Seung Ri.

378
00:19:47,203 --> 00:19:49,136
If you don't apologize,

379
00:19:49,136 --> 00:19:51,336
I'll keep pouring ice water
over myself every day.

380
00:19:53,403 --> 00:19:56,303
How exactly does he expect me
to apologize?

381
00:19:56,303 --> 00:19:58,203
Should I go and beg on my knees?

382
00:19:58,203 --> 00:19:59,636
I can't. Never.

383
00:20:00,203 --> 00:20:01,903
(Jeong Ran)

384
00:20:02,803 --> 00:20:04,336
What?

385
00:20:04,336 --> 00:20:07,103
Your daughter is just as precious
as Min Ho?

386
00:20:07,103 --> 00:20:09,903
How dare you compare her to my Min Ho?

387
00:20:13,303 --> 00:20:14,536
I almost pressed it.

388
00:20:17,303 --> 00:20:19,503
Anyway, what on earth is he doing?

389
00:20:19,503 --> 00:20:21,036
How come there's not even a single call?

390
00:20:21,036 --> 00:20:22,303
Seriously.

391
00:20:22,303 --> 00:20:23,436
Cheers!

392
00:20:27,303 --> 00:20:29,403
Hey, why the rush?

393
00:20:29,403 --> 00:20:31,236
You should clink glasses first.

394
00:20:31,236 --> 00:20:32,903
Seong Jun, cheers.

395
00:20:35,903 --> 00:20:37,103
Mr. Seo...

396
00:20:37,103 --> 00:20:38,903
No, Gwon Sik.

397
00:20:39,903 --> 00:20:41,703
This is a private gathering.

398
00:20:41,703 --> 00:20:44,003
Let's drop the ranks and talk.

399
00:20:44,736 --> 00:20:46,403
Make a position for Seong Jun.

400
00:20:47,103 --> 00:20:50,736
If I step in,
people will say it's favoritism.

401
00:20:50,736 --> 00:20:52,203
Ko Dae Chi.

402
00:20:52,903 --> 00:20:56,903
Come on. Is this really the time
to worry about pride?

403
00:20:56,903 --> 00:20:59,203
Maybe you're fine,

404
00:20:59,203 --> 00:21:01,936
but I'm not.

405
00:21:01,936 --> 00:21:03,236
Stop it.

406
00:21:03,236 --> 00:21:04,403
What?

407
00:21:04,403 --> 00:21:06,003
Stop what?

408
00:21:06,003 --> 00:21:08,103
A favor is only a favor
when the other person wants it.

409
00:21:10,303 --> 00:21:11,603
Hey.

410
00:21:11,603 --> 00:21:13,803
Don't stop halfway through your sentence.

411
00:21:13,803 --> 00:21:17,236
And what do you mean
by a favor they don't want?

412
00:21:17,236 --> 00:21:18,436
Haven't you done enough...

413
00:21:19,503 --> 00:21:20,703
these past couple of days?

414
00:21:20,703 --> 00:21:23,003
What did I do? What are you talking about?

415
00:21:23,836 --> 00:21:26,303
You really want to fight me?

416
00:21:26,303 --> 00:21:27,636
That's enough.

417
00:21:27,636 --> 00:21:30,903
We're turning 60 soon.
Why are you fighting?

418
00:21:33,236 --> 00:21:34,503
Do you think...

419
00:21:34,503 --> 00:21:37,136
I'm being arrogant in front of you?

420
00:21:37,136 --> 00:21:38,603
It's the opposite.

421
00:21:38,603 --> 00:21:41,603
You're looking down on me and mocking me.

422
00:21:41,603 --> 00:21:43,036
Ko Dae Chi, what are you saying?

423
00:21:43,036 --> 00:21:46,303
For you, top school graduates and all,

424
00:21:46,303 --> 00:21:50,003
I'm just some pathetic guy who took
the CEO seat thanks to his father...

425
00:21:50,003 --> 00:21:51,336
despite not being capable, right?

426
00:21:52,203 --> 00:21:53,636
Even now.

427
00:21:53,636 --> 00:21:54,703
As a friend, I'm trying to help,

428
00:21:54,703 --> 00:21:56,803
but you don't want
to be indebted to someone like me, right?

429
00:21:59,203 --> 00:22:02,003
Fine, I'll be honest.

430
00:22:03,603 --> 00:22:05,436
I don't want to meet you again...

431
00:22:07,203 --> 00:22:09,003
like this.

432
00:22:09,903 --> 00:22:12,303
I'm human too.

433
00:22:14,436 --> 00:22:16,336
My pride is hurt, and I feel miserable.

434
00:22:16,336 --> 00:22:17,536
Seong Jun.

435
00:22:17,536 --> 00:22:20,303
That's just an inferiority complex.

436
00:22:20,303 --> 00:22:21,803
Pride between us?

437
00:22:21,803 --> 00:22:23,003
What does that matter?

438
00:22:23,003 --> 00:22:24,103
Between us?

439
00:22:25,203 --> 00:22:26,303
What are we, exactly?

440
00:22:29,503 --> 00:22:30,503
Right.

441
00:22:32,103 --> 00:22:34,203
It is an inferiority complex.

442
00:22:36,603 --> 00:22:37,603
I'll leave first.

443
00:22:49,503 --> 00:22:52,036
Let's go now.

444
00:22:52,036 --> 00:22:55,503
Madam has been calling nonstop.

445
00:22:57,036 --> 00:22:58,736
I'm sleepy too.

446
00:22:58,736 --> 00:23:00,303
Mr. Ju,

447
00:23:00,303 --> 00:23:03,736
so are you saying
you should be guaranteed sleep?

448
00:23:06,203 --> 00:23:07,236
I'm leaving first.

449
00:23:08,103 --> 00:23:10,036
Hey, Seo Gwon Sik, sit down.

450
00:23:10,036 --> 00:23:11,303
- Wait...
- Sit down!

451
00:23:11,303 --> 00:23:12,736
Mr. Seo...

452
00:23:13,636 --> 00:23:16,736
What a waste of food!

453
00:23:17,103 --> 00:23:18,903
What a feast.

454
00:23:20,136 --> 00:23:22,736
Let's see, this is sea bream,

455
00:23:22,736 --> 00:23:24,103
this is flounder...

456
00:23:24,103 --> 00:23:25,603
Eat quietly.

457
00:23:25,603 --> 00:23:26,636
- Quietly.
- Seriously.

458
00:23:29,936 --> 00:23:31,603
Did you drink?

459
00:23:31,603 --> 00:23:33,736
With Min Ho's father?

460
00:23:33,736 --> 00:23:34,803
Yes.

461
00:23:36,003 --> 00:23:37,603
- You're back?
- Hey.

462
00:23:39,103 --> 00:23:40,403
You're drunk, Dad.

463
00:23:40,403 --> 00:23:41,403
Yeah.

464
00:23:41,403 --> 00:23:42,703
You're home.

465
00:23:42,703 --> 00:23:44,936
You had drinks after a long time.

466
00:23:44,936 --> 00:23:47,703
My son.

467
00:23:47,703 --> 00:23:49,836
Should I give you some allowance?

468
00:23:49,836 --> 00:23:51,136
Thank you.

469
00:23:51,703 --> 00:23:53,003
No, Dad!

470
00:23:53,003 --> 00:23:55,103
I already give Seung Wu an allowance.

471
00:23:55,103 --> 00:23:57,303
- Seung Ri!
- You brat.

472
00:23:57,303 --> 00:23:59,803
You take money from me every month,
and now from your sister too?

473
00:23:59,803 --> 00:24:01,203
Come on!

474
00:24:01,203 --> 00:24:03,636
Can you even understand
this artist's empty soul?

475
00:24:04,603 --> 00:24:07,303
Be quiet and promise me one thing.

476
00:24:07,303 --> 00:24:09,003
Starting this week,

477
00:24:09,003 --> 00:24:10,703
report your work progress once a week.

478
00:24:11,303 --> 00:24:13,136
Otherwise, no allowance at all.

479
00:24:13,836 --> 00:24:15,903
Don't give him any allowance anymore.

480
00:24:15,903 --> 00:24:18,136
Hey, Seo Seung Ri!

481
00:24:18,136 --> 00:24:20,103
What did you just say?

482
00:24:20,103 --> 00:24:22,203
You need to get hit
to come to your senses.

483
00:24:22,203 --> 00:24:23,203
Go ahead, hit me.

484
00:24:23,203 --> 00:24:25,903
I'll smash everything.

485
00:24:30,303 --> 00:24:32,103
When will he grow up?

486
00:24:33,103 --> 00:24:36,436
Let Seung Wu do what he wants,

487
00:24:36,436 --> 00:24:39,203
as long as you guide him well.

488
00:24:39,203 --> 00:24:40,603
Dad, Seung Wu...

489
00:24:40,603 --> 00:24:43,136
He has his own dream.

490
00:24:43,136 --> 00:24:47,203
Being able to dream
is something incredible.

491
00:24:49,403 --> 00:24:51,303
I'm tired, so I'll head in.

492
00:24:52,836 --> 00:24:55,703
Your dad must be going through something.

493
00:24:56,403 --> 00:24:58,936
He's been talking a lot lately.

494
00:26:03,603 --> 00:26:05,303
I need to get those documents...

495
00:26:05,303 --> 00:26:08,936
to respond or refute this.

496
00:26:08,936 --> 00:26:10,536
You said it was a lucky charm.

497
00:26:10,536 --> 00:26:13,336
Give me luck!

498
00:26:13,336 --> 00:26:15,403
Please!

499
00:26:41,303 --> 00:26:42,736
Liar.

500
00:26:43,603 --> 00:26:45,903
You said you'd build me a house
with ice cream sticks.

501
00:26:48,903 --> 00:26:50,803
(Yugwang Apartment Construction Site)

502
00:26:50,803 --> 00:26:52,203
Hey, kid.

503
00:26:52,203 --> 00:26:54,936
It's dangerous here. Get out.

504
00:26:54,936 --> 00:26:57,436
Is Gyeol here?

505
00:26:57,436 --> 00:26:59,303
Gyeol? Who's that?

506
00:26:59,303 --> 00:27:02,103
His dad is in charge here.

507
00:27:02,436 --> 00:27:05,003
He said he comes here every Saturday.

508
00:27:09,136 --> 00:27:12,003
You mean Manager Han Sun Cheon's son,
Gyeol?

509
00:27:12,003 --> 00:27:13,303
He doesn't come here anymore.

510
00:27:13,303 --> 00:27:14,703
What? Why?

511
00:27:15,603 --> 00:27:16,803
My goodness.

512
00:27:17,836 --> 00:27:19,636
Go on, leave.

513
00:27:19,636 --> 00:27:21,103
It's dangerous. Hurry.

514
00:27:21,103 --> 00:27:22,303
Let's go.

515
00:27:22,303 --> 00:27:24,103
That way. Bye.

516
00:27:24,103 --> 00:27:25,336
So mean.

517
00:27:26,236 --> 00:27:27,836
Liar.

518
00:27:40,403 --> 00:27:42,703
Ma'am, what's wrong?

519
00:27:42,703 --> 00:27:43,803
What do I do?

520
00:27:44,403 --> 00:27:45,803
Ma'am, what's wrong?

521
00:27:47,703 --> 00:27:49,136
Please wake up.

522
00:27:49,136 --> 00:27:50,836
Ma'am!

523
00:27:55,536 --> 00:27:58,336
(Our Happy Days)

524
00:27:58,336 --> 00:28:00,803
Please guide me well.

525
00:28:00,803 --> 00:28:02,736
He hasn't changed at all,
always drawing the line.

526
00:28:02,736 --> 00:28:04,403
If you truly love someone,

527
00:28:04,403 --> 00:28:06,603
shouldn't you
respect their feelings first?

528
00:28:07,703 --> 00:28:09,403
What are you doing? Let go of my hand!

529
00:28:09,403 --> 00:28:10,503
What a creep!

530
00:28:11,003 --> 00:28:12,936
You can go into that room, right?

531
00:28:12,936 --> 00:28:14,503
Pretend to clean and sneak in.

532
00:28:14,503 --> 00:28:15,203
No!

533
00:28:15,203 --> 00:28:16,903
I'm sorry, Dad.

534
00:28:16,903 --> 00:28:18,403
I'll put it back right away.

535
00:28:18,403 --> 00:28:20,153
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
